{"TopicId":162396,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"SPH -\u0026gt; VAB causing headaches","CreatedByName":"Loren Pechtel","CreatedById":157006,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-22T00:13:06Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Loren Pechtel","CreatedById":157006,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-22T00:13:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI built a rover in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E, took it over to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E and I\u0027m trying to strap boosters to it to get it to where it\u0027s going.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve done this before by putting a docking port on the top of the rover and decoupling when it was down but this time I tried to do it by directly coupling the boosters to the side of the rover.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnfortunately it\u0027s determined to put one part right side up and one part upside-down.\u00A0 That\u0027s very nasty for getting everything nicely balanced for flight!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny way around this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cpt Kerbalkrunch","CreatedById":175588,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-22T00:28:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeing that it was built in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E, did you try mirrored symmetry? If I remember right, that\u0027s what I did with rovers moved over to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Loren Pechtel","CreatedById":157006,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-22T00:35:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223099293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022162396\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221498091302\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022175588\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cpt Kerbalkrunch\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Cpt Kerbalkrunch said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeing that it was built in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E, did you try mirrored symmetry? If I remember right, that\u0027s what I did with rovers moved over to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat mirrored symmetry in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cpt Kerbalkrunch","CreatedById":175588,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-22T00:43:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223099301\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022162396\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221498091729\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157006\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Loren Pechtel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Loren Pechtel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat mirrored symmetry in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust hit the R button to switch from radial to mirrored symmetry. That should do it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-22T00:45:12Z\u0022 title=\u002206/22/2017 12:45  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 22, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Cpt Kerbalkrunch\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"qzgy","CreatedById":160994,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-22T03:56:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure I understand the question. Could be the whole symmetry issue. Mind showing us pictures?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}